Meta-analysis
The 11 included articles were classified according to the type of 
sleep microstructure analysis performed in the study and the 
type of quantitative outcome available for inclusion. Twenty-
nine different meta-analyses were performed to assess the 
effect of each of the following continuous variables:
	-	 Twenty-three parameters of Cyclic Alternating Pattern 
(CAP) analysis (n  =  3 studies): total CAP rate in NREM, 
NREM1, NREM2, and NREM3 sleep (percentage of NREM, 
NREM1, NREM2, and NREM3 sleep time occupied by CAP 
sequences); CAP A1, A2, and A3 rates in NREM sleep (per-
centage of NREM sleep time occupied by CAP A1, A2, and 
A3 sequences); CAP A1, A2, and A3 indexes (number of A1, 
A2, and A3 phases per hour of NREM, NREM1, NREM2, and 
NREM3 sleep); duration of A and B phases; number and du-
ration of CAP sequences;
	-	 Four parameters of sleep EEG power analysis: slow wave ac-
tivity (SWA, i.e. EEG power in the delta band during NREM 
sleep) (n = 6 studies); spindle activity (SpA, i.e. EEG power in 
the sigma band during NREM sleep) (n = three studies); theta 
activity (ThA, i.e. EEG power in the theta band during REM) 
(n = 2 studies);
	-	 One parameter of sleep graphoelements analysis (n  =  2 
studies): spindle density (SpD, i.e. number of sleep spindles 
per time unit of NREM2 sleep).
